furcate-pi-minima
Copyright 2026 Furcate Contributors

This product includes software developed at Furcate (https://furcate.xyz).

This crate is a Pi-class operator wrapper that supervises an unmodified
upstream Minima full node. It is not a fork or reimplementation of
Minima; it fetches and runs the upstream `minima.jar` published at
https://github.com/minima-global/Minima under Apache-2.0.

This product depends on the following third-party software:
  - Minima (https://github.com/minima-global/Minima) — Apache-2.0
    (downloaded at runtime as `minima.jar`; not redistributed in source form)
  - reqwest (https://github.com/seanmonstar/reqwest) — MIT/Apache-2.0
  - tokio (https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio) — MIT
  - clap (https://github.com/clap-rs/clap) — MIT/Apache-2.0
  - rustls (https://github.com/rustls/rustls) — MIT/Apache-2.0/ISC
  - secrecy (https://github.com/iqlusioninc/crates) — MIT/Apache-2.0
  - minima-attest (https://github.com/furcateai/minima-attest) — Apache-2.0
    (loaded only when the `minima-attest` feature is enabled)
